<h3>European Union Users</h3>

<p>If you are a consumer resident in the European Union, you will benefit from any mandatory provisions of the law of the country in which you are resident. Nothing in these Terms affects your rights as a consumer to rely on such mandatory local law provisions.</p>

<p><strong>EU Consumer Rights:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Unfair Terms:</strong> Any terms that are deemed unfair under EU consumer protection laws will not apply to you</li>
    <li><strong>Right of Withdrawal:</strong> For digital content and services, you have a 14-day right of withdrawal from the date of purchase, unless you have given express consent to begin performance and acknowledged that you will lose your right of withdrawal</li>
    <li><strong>Conformity:</strong> Digital content and services must conform to the contract and be fit for the purposes for which they would normally be used</li>
    <li><strong>Remedies:</strong> If digital content or services are not in conformity with the contract, you have the right to have them brought into conformity, have the price reduced, or terminate the contract</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Online Dispute Resolution:</strong></p>
<p>The European Commission provides an online dispute resolution platform, which you can access at <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/</a>. If you are an EU consumer and wish to use this platform to resolve disputes, you may do so.</p>

<p><strong>Applicable Law for EU Consumers:</strong></p>
<p>Where you are a consumer resident in the European Union, the governing law provisions in these Terms do not deprive you of the protection afforded to you by provisions that cannot be derogated from by agreement by virtue of the law of the Member State in which you are resident.</p>
